   <h1>Coffee Pot Pergola</h1>

   <h3>Lake City Neighborhood<br /> Seattle, WA </h3>


   <img src="coffeePot/coffeePot1screen.jpg">

   <h4>Funding Source: Seattle Office of Arts and Cultural Affairs & Seattle Department of Transportation</h4>
   
   <br /> 

   <div class='bold_text'>

    Lake City is a Seattle neighborhood known for its fast food venues, eclectic shops, car dealerships
    and fast-moving traffic.  Behind its flashy fa&ccedil;ade, however, lie deep ravines with native vegetation and
    salmon-bearing streams. Lake City also has a rich past as an idyllic retreat for weary urban dwellers.
    The artist imagined campers drinking coffee around a campfire at the artwork site where currently resides a
    bustling cafe. These and other real and imagined inspirations evolved in the
    mind's eye of the artist and resulted in this local landmark and outdoor eating venue.
    


   </div>
   
